---
@version: [2, current]
@description: Add, remove and update the current query string URL keys and values.
@lot:
  - array $query = null, array $c = ['?', '&amp;', '=', ""]
  - array $query = null, string $separator = '&amp;'
@static: 1
@example: |
  // → ?a=b&c=d&e=[f]=g
  echo HTTP::query(['c' => 1000]);
@result: |
  '?a=b&amp;c=1000&amp;e=[f]=g'
...

> **Note:** Setting the property value to `true` will insert a query string without any value, setting the property value to the string `"true"` will insert a query string with value `true`:
>
> ~~~ .php
> // → ?a=b
> echo HTTP::query([
>     'c' => true,
>     'd' => 'true'
> ]);
> ~~~
>
> **Result:**
>
> ~~~ .txt
> ?a=b&amp;c&amp;d=true
> ~~~
>
> Setting the property value to `false` or `null` will remove the query string, setting the property value to the string `"false"` will insert a query string with value `false`:
>
> ~~~ .php
> // → ?a=b
> echo HTTP::query([
>     'a' => false,
>     'c' => 'false'
> ]);
> ~~~
>
> **Result:**
>
> ~~~ .txt
> ?c=false
> ~~~